{
  "texts": [
    "• Lack of structural modeling.",
    "LLMs lack the capability to explicitly model graph structures in the same way that GNN does.",
    "Merely relying on contextual descriptions to acquire information may not be adequate and direct.",
    "Therefore, additional investigation is required to improve LLMs' ability to model graph topology.",
    "ConclusionDynamic graph neural networks, a recent development in representation learning, can process changing graph structures and have potential applications across various fields."
  ]
}